<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-2082] Saved row cache continues to be read past max cache size</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2082</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Scenario:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Node has a saved row cache of size n&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;node OOMs&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Make row cache size = .5n to prevent OOM while we debug, restart node.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;n items are still read from the row cache, making startup take twice as long as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;



&lt;p&gt;(This is intended as a straightforward bug, not as a hackish &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1966&quot; title=&quot;Option to control how many items are read on cache load&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1966&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1966&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.)&lt;/p&gt;</description>
