                            <comment id="13069679" author="cburroughs" created="Fri, 22 Jul 2011 19:00:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that the second patch applies on top of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-1966&quot; title=&quot;Option to control how many items are read on cache load&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-1966&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-1966&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13071283" author="jbellis" created="Tue, 26 Jul 2011 18:58:40 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed since the code involved is small, but I note that the applicability is limited because you can&apos;t change the cache setting via schema or JMX until the node has started successfully.  So it&apos;s only useful if you notice memory pressure and change the setting before the node OOMs.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13071297" author="hudson" created="Tue, 26 Jul 2011 19:19:38 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Cassandra #975 (See &lt;a href=&quot;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra/975/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://builds.apache.org/job/Cassandra/975/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
    stop reading cache after max size-to-save is reached&lt;br/&gt;
patch by Chris Burroughs; reviewed by jbellis for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-2082&quot; title=&quot;Saved row cache continues to be read past max cache size&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-2082&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-2082&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

